About

Scott has about 2 years of experience as a Software Engineer. He has experience developing website and web applications using a variety of technologies. Scott has experience in tersting and integration, writing tests and setting up a continuous development enviornment. He has experience using the Agile Scrum Methodology as a team lead and developer.

Education
University of Maryland, Baltimore County

Scott graduated from UMBC in May of 2017 with a BS in Information Systems.

Scott's favorite class during his college career was "Independent Research". In this class he collaborated with a research professor at UMBC as well as with a professor and student combo from another college. The research was to figure out if we could determine malitous website visitors using data-mining (specifically clustering). The preprocessing of data was done with Python and the clustering was done with R. During the end of his time at UMBC, he presented his data at a school event.

Scott was part of "UMBC Rockets and More", a club about doing fun things with science with a focus on Rockets. During his 3rd year he became president of the club. He was in charge of the organizing club activities and outreach events, presenting and justifying the budget for funding and maintaining the budget.
